[src:pyyaml-parsing/pyyamldocumentation-p02] `Dumper.add_multi_representer(base_data_type, multi_representer)`: see `add_multi_representer`.
[src:pyyaml-parsing/pyyamldocumentation-p02] `Dumper.represent_scalar(tag, value, style=None)` returns a scalar node with the given `tag`, `value`, and `style`.
[src:pyyaml-parsing/pyyamldocumentation-p02] This function is intended to be used in representers.
[src:pyyaml-parsing/pyyamldocumentation-p02] `Dumper.represent_sequence(tag, sequence, flow_style=None)` return a sequence node with the given `tag` and subnodes generated from the items of the given `sequence`.
[src:pyyaml-parsing/pyyamldocumentation-p02] `Dumper.represent_mapping(tag, mapping, flow_style=None)` return a mapping node with the given `tag` and subnodes generated from the keys and values of the given `mapping`.
[src:pyyaml-parsing/pyyamldocumentation-p02] `Dumper.add_implicit_resolver(tag, regexp, first)`: see `add_implicit_resolver`.
[src:pyyaml-parsing/pyyamldocumentation-p02] `Dumper.add_path_resolver(tag, path, kind)`: see `add_path_resolver`.
